children.subject: I bought tickets for my guests. Did I need to buy a ticket for myself as well? Or will we just need to show ID to get in?

history.content:
Dear Berkeley Engineer, 

Congratulations! You're almost done and we are so excited to celebrate your accomplishment with you at the COE Commencement ceremony on Tuesday, May 16th. If you have already registered for commencement, please disregard this email. 
If you have not registered for commencement - the deadline is THIS FRIDAY, April 21st! Registering for commencement only takes a few minutes and must be done before Friday to ensure your name will be printed in the programs handed out at the ceremony. 
Once you register, you will be emailed a link to purchase tickets. Students that do not register by April 21st are not guaranteed the maximum number of tickets and their names will not be in the printed program.
Register Here!
Information regarding commencement ticketing, parking, ADA accommodations, etc. can be found at the bottom of the commencement webpage. 
If you have any questions regarding commencement please send an email to bears@berkeley.edu 
Congratulations again and GO BEARS!
